# Local dev defaults. For Play Store / release APK+AAB builds, copy `.env.production.example`
# → `.env.production` (gitignored) and run `npm run build:mobile:prod` — that picks up
# VITE_TARGET=capacitor and prod Supabase URL/key.
#
# Supabase – MUST be same as main ERP (web) so one database, same login.
# Copy VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY from project root .env.production or .env.local.
#
# Local dev URL:
#   - Recommended: VITE_SUPABASE_URL=http://localhost:5174 (Vite proxy → Kong)
#   - Or leave https://supabase.dincouture.pk — dev browser auto-uses same-origin proxy
# Production PWA / native builds: direct https://supabase.dincouture.pk (see deploy + resolveSupabaseApiUrl.ts)
#
# Do NOT use the public Supabase tutorial anon JWT (iss "supabase-demo").
# Optional: VITE_DISABLE_REALTIME=true — turn off postgres_changes from localhost.
# Optional: VITE_SUPABASE_PROXY_ORIGIN=https://erp.dincouture.pk — Origin header on Vite→Kong proxy leg.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=http://localhost:5174
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-from-web-app

# Pay Supplier RPC fixes (same Postgres as web): paste migrations/rollups/record_payment_allocation_fix_bundle.sql in Supabase SQL Editor once if Pay refs fail.
